.Dd September 7, 2015
.Dt CTRLALTDEL 8
.Os ubase 0.1
.Sh NAME
.Nm ctrlaltdel
.Nd toggle Ctrl-Alt-Del behaviour
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Fl h | s
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
toggles the function of Ctrl-Alt-Del based on the two choices given in
.Pa linux/kernel/sys.c :
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It hard reset
reboot the computer immediately without calling
.Xr sync 2 .
.It soft reset
send SIGINT to
.Xr init 8 .
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
Set to hard reset.
.It Fl s
Set to soft reset.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sync 2 ,
.Xr init 8
